    "created_at": "2015-09-18T02:36:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-18T02:36:29Z",
    "body": "There is no magic to pause everything automatically, Chromium took the way of destroying background tabs to reduce memory usages, which is very similar to your unloading/reloading webview.\n\nOn Windows and Linux the traditional way is to pause the loops when window is blurred, but you have to do it yourself.\n\nI'm closing this since we can not provide a builtin solution.\n"
