    "created_at": "2015-09-21T02:38:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-21T02:38:43Z",
    "body": "> Chromium implemented it by destroying the tab when it is not visited for sometime, and then reload it when you open it\n\nCan someone do this solely with the given Electron API though? I have to imagine that Chromium doesn't lose things like scroll state or the JS context when the page is blown away then reloaded, no? I'm :+1: on letting developers control policy but we should give them the tools to do so\n"
